'''Hayes Alan Jenkins''' (born March 23, 1933 in [[Akron, Ohio]]), an [[United States|American]] [[Figure skating|figure skater]], led men's skating for 4 years, 1953-56.  He won four consecutive [[World Figure Skating Championships]] from 1953 to 1956. He also won the gold medal in the [[1956 Winter Olympics]], after placing 4th in the [[1952 Winter Olympics]].  His brother [[David Jenkins (figure skater)|David Jenkins]] won the gold in [[1960 Winter Olympics|1960]]. Jenkins later married [[Carol Heiss]], the [[Figure skating at the 1956 Winter Olympics|1956 Olympic silver medalist]] and the [[Figure skating at the 1960 Winter Olympics|1960 Olympic gold medalist]].<ref name=fp261>Findling and Pelle (1996), p. 261</ref>

